==============================================
Installing ONIE on Alpha_Networks SNX60A0-486F
==============================================

Cross-Compiling ONIE
====================

Change directories to ``build-config`` to compile ONIE.

To compile ONIE first change directories to ``build-config`` and then
type ``"make MACHINEROOT=../machine/alphanetworks  MACHINE=alphanetworks_snx60a0_486f all"``.
For example::

  $ cd build-config
  $ make -j4 MACHINEROOT=../machine/alphanetworks  MACHINE=alphanetworks_snx60a0_486f all

When complete, the ONIE binaries are located in
``build/images``::

-rw-r--r-- 1 5352112 Aug 19 12:01 alphanetworks_snx60a0_486f-r0.initrd
-rw-r--r-- 1 3347520 Aug 19 11:44 alphanetworks_snx60a0_486f-r0.vmlinuz
-rw-r--r-- 1 8715893 Aug 19 12:01 onie-updater-x86_64-alphanetworks_snx60a0_486f-r0
-rw-r--r-- 1 18874368 Aug 19 13:58 onie-recovery-x86_64-alphanetworks_snx60a0_486f-r0.iso

alphanetworks_snx60a0_486f-r0.vmlinuz -- This is the ONIE kernel image

alphanetworks_snx60a0_486f-r0.initrd  -- This is the ONIE initramfs (filesystem)

onie-updater-x86_64-alphanetworks_snx60a0_486f-r0 -- This is the ONIE self-update
image.  This image is a self-extracting archive used for installing ONIE.
